340 g Turkey Breast Portions
80 g Tomato
1 unit Gala Apple
1 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
2 tbsp Oil*
½ tbsp Seasoned Salt
1 tsp Sugar*
113 g Baby Spinach
56 g Carrot, julienned

Before starting, wash and dry all produce. Pat turkey dry with paper towels. Sprinkle half the seasoned salt over turkey (all for 4 ppl), then season with pepper.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then turkey. Cook until golden-brown and cooked through, 3-5 min per side.** Transfer turkey to a clean cutting board to rest for 2-3 min.

Cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces. Core, then cut apple into 1/4-inch slices.

Whisk together mayo, vinegar, 1 tsp sugar and 1 tbsp oil (dbl both for 4 ppl) in a large bowl.

Add baby spinach, apples, tomatoes and carrots to the bowl with dressing. Season with salt and pepper, to taste, then toss to combine.

Thinly slice turkey. Divide salad between plates. Top salad with turkey. Sprinkle feta over top.